[Heat waves in the USA and the EU caused clusters
of cases of _Vibrio_ infections either
transmitted from direct contact with the salt or
brackish water or from shellfish.
The Oosterschelde (Eastern Scheldt) is an estuary
in Zeeland, the Netherlands, between
Schouwen-Duiveland and Tholen on the north and
Noord-Beveland and Zuid-Beveland on the south.
Its location can be seen at:
<http://www.kbs-koeln.de/hauptschule-borsigstrasse/oosterschelde.jpg>
- Mod.LL]
